[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: Software integration
OPTIONS:
  MARKUP: Text

[GRAMMAR]
IMPORT_FROM_FILE: en_50716_grammar.sgra

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This document covers the Integration phase for the software element of
the railway control and protection system identified below. It is prepared
in accordance with EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.6 (Integration), and collects
three output deliverables from Table A.1:

  21. Software Integration Test Report
  22. Software/Hardware Integration Test Report
  23. Software Integration Verification Report

BASIC and SIL_1 through SIL_4 fields are taken from EN 50716:2023:
- Table A.1 (docs 21, 22, 23): BASIC=R, SIL_1–4=HR.
- Table A.6 (integration techniques):
    Dynamic analysis (A.13): BASIC=HR, SIL_1–4=HR.
    Performance testing (A.18): BASIC=--, SIL_1=R, SIL_2=R, SIL_3=HR, SIL_4=HR.

ITR-xxx are executed SW-integration test cases; HITR-xxx are executed
HW-SW integration test cases. Both series are the executed counterparts
of the SWIT-xxx and HWIT-xxx specification entries in 03_architecture_design.sdoc.

Instructions for use:
- UIDs follow convention: INT-xxx (requirements), ITR-xxx (SW integration
  test cases), HITR-xxx (HW-SW integration test cases).
- Duplicate ITR and HITR entries for each executed test case.
- Delete this instruction block before formal release.
<<<

