[[SECTION]]
TITLE: SW integration test cases executed

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The following ITR-xxx entries are executed counterparts of the SWIT-xxx
specification entries in 03_architecture_design.sdoc. Duplicate for each
executed test case; populate ACTUAL_RESULT and set VERDICT upon execution.
<<<

[TEST_CASE]
UID: ITR-001
STATUS: Active
TITLE: <Module A> – <Module B> interface: nominal data exchange
TEST_TYPE: Integration
PRECONDITIONS: >>>
- <Module A> and <Module B> integrated and initialised (Step 2 of sequence).
- Input <DataItem_1> set to nominal value <nominal_value> within [<min>..<max>].
- No fault flags active; no prior error state.
- Integration stubs for not-yet-integrated modules in place; confirmed they
  do not mask the interface under test.
<<<
STEPS: >>>
1. Set <DataItem_1> = <nominal_value>.
2. Trigger one execution cycle of <Module A>.
3. Read <output_param_1> from <Module B>'s interface.
4. Record return code from <Module B>.
5. Check fault log and system state.
<<<
EXPECTED_RESULT: >>>
- <output_param_1> = <expected_value> ± <tolerance>.
- Return code: OK.
- No assertions triggered; no fault log entries.
- Execution completed within one cycle (< <n> ms).
<<<
ACTUAL_RESULT: >>>
- <output_param_1> = <measured_value> (<expected_value> ± <tolerance>). WITHIN LIMIT.
- Return code: OK. PASS.
- Fault log entries: 0. PASS.
- Cycle time: <measured_cycle_time> ms (limit: <n> ms). WITHIN LIMIT.
No inter-module data corruption detected by integrity check (SAD-032). PASS.
<<<
VERDICT: PASS
DATE_EXECUTED: <YYYY-MM-DD>
TESTER: <Name>
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SRS-031
  ROLE: Verifies

[TEST_CASE]
UID: ITR-002
STATUS: Active
TITLE: <Module A> – <Module B> interface: out-of-range input rejection
TEST_TYPE: Integration
PRECONDITIONS: >>>
- <Module A> and <Module B> integrated and initialised.
- System in normal operating state.
<<<
STEPS: >>>
1. Set <DataItem_1> = <value outside valid range, max + 1>.
2. Trigger one execution cycle of <Module A>.
3. Read return code and fault log from <Module B>.
4. Read system state after one additional execution cycle.
5. Remove out-of-range stimulus; apply nominal value; trigger one cycle.
<<<
EXPECTED_RESULT: >>>
- Return code: ERR_RANGE.
- <Module B> adopts safe output state.
- Fault log entry created with correct code and timestamp.
- No uncontrolled exception or watchdog timeout.
- Step 5: return OK; normal operation resumes.
<<<
ACTUAL_RESULT: >>>
- Return code: ERR_RANGE. PASS.
- <Module B> output: <safe_default_value> (safe state). PASS.
- Fault log: 1 entry, code <FC-xx>, timestamp <HH:MM:SS.mmm>. PASS.
- No exception or watchdog timeout detected during error state. PASS.
- Step 5: return OK; <output_param_1> = <expected_value>. PASS.
Recovery to normal operation confirmed within one cycle. PASS.
<<<
VERDICT: PASS
DATE_EXECUTED: <YYYY-MM-DD>
TESTER: <Name>
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SRS-031
  ROLE: Verifies

