    at integration boundary  |         | (CD-031)               |

Shared data integrity: All accesses to shared data items protected by the
mechanisms defined in SAD-020 (mutual exclusion / double-buffer). No data
corruption observed during concurrent-access tests.

Error propagation: Out-of-range and hardware error conditions injected at
each interface boundary propagated correctly through the integrated software
without causing uncontrolled exceptions or incorrect output states.
