[ACTION_ITEM]
UID: PR-IT-001
STATUS: Closed
TITLE: <Module A>/<Module B> shared data: stale value not detected when <Module A> skips a cycle
STATEMENT: >>>
Defect found during ITR-002 (concurrent-access test). When <Module A>
failed to complete its cycle within the scheduling window, <Module B> read
a stale copy of <DataItem_2> without triggering the staleness detector.
Impact: output based on outdated data; potential safety impact assessed as
<Minor / Major — state assessment>.
Fix applied: staleness counter incremented each cycle; <Module B> checks
counter before consuming data; ERR_STALE returned and safe state applied
if counter exceeds threshold.
Re-test: ITR-001 and concurrent-access test re-executed after fix; PASS.
<<<
OWNER: <Developer Name>
DUE_DATE: <YYYY-MM-DD>
COMMENT: >>>
Fixed in source revision <hash>. Staleness detection now verified by
dedicated test case ITR-003 (add entry for each project). Static analysis
rule added to flag direct shared-variable reads without counter check.
<<<

