[[SECTION]]
TITLE: HW-SW integration test cases executed

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The following HITR-xxx entries are executed counterparts of the HWIT-xxx
specification entries in 03_architecture_design.sdoc. Duplicate for each
executed test case; populate ACTUAL_RESULT and set VERDICT upon execution.
<<<

[TEST_CASE]
UID: HITR-001
STATUS: Active
TITLE: Watchdog timer: refresh and timeout behaviour on target hardware
TEST_TYPE: HW-SW-Integration
PRECONDITIONS: >>>
- Target hardware powered; firmware loaded from baseline <SW-BL-xxx>.
- Watchdog configured to <n> ms timeout (hardware register confirmed).
- System in normal operating state; safety task executing cyclically.
- Debug probe connected for step-inhibit capability.
<<<
STEPS: >>>
1. Observe normal operation for <n> cycles (<n> ms); record watchdog refresh
   calls per cycle using logic analyser channel <n>.
2. Via debug probe, inhibit the watchdog refresh call for one cycle.
3. Monitor system outputs and debug UART for up to <n + margin> ms.
4. Restore normal watchdog refresh; observe recovery behaviour.
5. Read fault log from non-volatile storage.
<<<
EXPECTED_RESULT: >>>
Step 1: Watchdog refresh observed every <period> ms ± <jitter>; no reset.
Step 3: Hardware reset or fail-safe output activation within <n> ms of
        missed refresh; system enters safe state.
Step 4: System re-initialises; remains in safe state pending fault clearance.
Step 5: Fault log entry for watchdog timeout event with timestamp.
<<<
ACTUAL_RESULT: >>>
Step 1: Watchdog refresh confirmed at <measured_period> ms (spec: <n> ± <jitter> ms).
        <n> cycles observed; 0 spurious resets. PASS.
Step 3: Hardware reset triggered at <measured_timeout> ms after missed refresh
        (spec: < <n> ms). Fail-safe outputs activated simultaneously. PASS.
Step 4: System re-initialised in <measured_reboot_time> ms; safe state maintained.
        No spurious output activation during reboot. PASS.
Step 5: Fault log entry: code WD-TIMEOUT, timestamp <HH:MM:SS.mmm>. PASS.
All expected safe-state conditions confirmed on logic analyser and oscilloscope.
<<<
VERDICT: PASS
DATE_EXECUTED: <YYYY-MM-DD>
TESTER: <Name>
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SRS-030
  ROLE: Verifies

[TEST_CASE]
UID: HITR-002
STATUS: Active
TITLE: Digital I/O interface: output command, readback, and loss-of-readback detection
TEST_TYPE: HW-SW-Integration
PRECONDITIONS: >>>
- Target hardware powered; firmware loaded from baseline <SW-BL-xxx>.
- Digital output channel <n> looped back to digital input channel <m>
  via test rig wiring.
- System in normal operating state; output in de-energised (safe) state.
<<<
STEPS: >>>
1. Software commands output channel <n> to the energised state.
2. After <n> ms, read back input channel <m>; record measured state.
3. Software commands output channel <n> to the de-energised state.
4. After <n> ms, read back input channel <m>; record measured state.
5. Disconnect loopback wire at output terminal; allow one full cycle.
6. Record system response: fault log, output state, system state.
<<<
EXPECTED_RESULT: >>>
Step 2: Input <m> reads ENERGISED; no fault logged.
Step 4: Input <m> reads DE-ENERGISED; no fault logged.
Step 6: Output-readback mismatch detected within one cycle;
        fault logged; output commanded to safe (de-energised) state.
        No watchdog timeout or uncontrolled state change.
<<<
ACTUAL_RESULT: >>>
Step 2: Input <m>: ENERGISED (measured voltage: <V> V, threshold: <V> V). PASS.
        No fault log entries. PASS.
Step 4: Input <m>: DE-ENERGISED (measured voltage: <V> V). PASS.
        No fault log entries. PASS.
Step 6: Mismatch detected after <measured_cycles> cycle(s) (limit: 1). PASS.
        Fault log: code IO-READBACK-MISMATCH, timestamp <HH:MM:SS.mmm>. PASS.
        Output channel <n>: DE-ENERGISED (confirmed by logic analyser). PASS.
        System state: SAFE-STATE. No watchdog timeout. PASS.
<<<
VERDICT: PASS
DATE_EXECUTED: <YYYY-MM-DD>
TESTER: <Name>
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SRS-030
  ROLE: Verifies

