[ACTION_ITEM]
UID: PR-HIT-001
STATUS: Closed
TITLE: Digital output readback: mismatch detected one cycle late under maximum interrupt load
STATEMENT: >>>
Defect found during HITR-002 (step 6) under maximum system load (all tasks
and ISRs running at peak rate). Readback mismatch for output channel <n>
was detected after 2 cycles instead of the required 1 cycle when the
diagnostics task was preempted by a burst of comms interrupts.
Impact: <n> ms additional latency in fault detection; assessed against
SRS-041 timing requirement — <within / exceeds> the total response time budget.
Fix applied: diagnostics task priority raised to prevent preemption by
non-safety comms ISR during the readback check window; scheduling analysis
(SAD-021) updated and re-verified.
Re-test: HITR-002 re-executed under maximum load after fix; PASS (1 cycle).
<<<
OWNER: <Developer Name>
DUE_DATE: <YYYY-MM-DD>
COMMENT: >>>
Fixed in source revision <hash>. Task scheduling analysis document updated.
WCET measurements (INT-050) repeated after priority change; all within budget.
<<<

