[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This section constitutes the Software Integration Verification Report as
required by EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.6 and Table A.1 (document 23). It
records the outcome of independent verification of the SW Integration Test
Report (section 2) and the HW-SW Integration Test Report (section 3) before
both reports are formally released and validation (EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.7)
commences.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: INT-070
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Verification scope and method
STATEMENT: >>>
The integration verification shall cover all deliverables in this document:

  a) SW Integration Test Report (section 2):
       - Completeness: all SWIT-xxx test cases from the integration test
         specification (SAD-070) have a corresponding executed ITR-xxx entry.
       - All ITR-xxx test cases show PASS verdict.
       - Interface coverage (INT-020): all interfaces in SAD-061 register
         are exercised.
       - Dynamic analysis results (INT-021): all required A.6 techniques
         applied and results PASS.
       - All PRs closed or safety-assessed (INT-030).

  b) SW/HW Integration Test Report (section 3):
       - Completeness: all HWIT-xxx specification cases have a corresponding
         executed HITR-xxx entry.
       - All HITR-xxx test cases show PASS verdict.
       - Performance requirements (SRS-040, SRS-041) met with positive margin
         in INT-050 and INT-051.
       - Communication link timing confirmed (INT-051).
       - All PRs closed or safety-assessed (INT-060).

  c) Consistency between the two reports and with the source code baseline
     (CI-010): the same baseline was used throughout all integration tests.

Verification method: structured inspection by the Software Verifier (SP-021)
using a checklist derived from EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.6.
Verifier: <Name, Organisation, independence evidence — see SP-021>
Checklist reference: <document ID or tool reference>
